The course consists of three modules:
1. Estonian for special purposes: characteristics of spoken and written text; specialty language; information retrieval; reading specialty texts
2. Academic text: planning the writing process (preparation, outline, rough draft, feedback, final draft); reading academic texts; summarizing and citing, referencing and reference management, revising the text (structure of the paragraph, phrasing, word choice)
3. Academic presentation: designing, compiling and presenting a slide show or a poster. 

The content of the modules is customized according to the study group.

The course includes individual and group work, during which students give feedback to their partners and make changes in their texts based on the feedback received.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to provide students with basic knowledge and skills for writing academic texts and giving presentations.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon completion of the course students can: - plan their writing process (setting goals; time management); - evaluate whether texts written by themselves or others meet the requirements of academic convention, including requirements for summarizing and referencing; - write well-structured texts with good style using relevant sources of practical language management; - give and receive feedback and make changes in their writing process based on it; - apply methods that support presentation when giving academic presentations; - format their texts according to the guidelines of their specialty or conventions of their field.
